-- Barclays Hires Ex-Morgan Stanley Investment Banker Tsutomu Ueki in Japan
-- B y   S h i g e r u   S a t o   a n d   T a k a k o   T a n i g u c h i
-- 2010-11-05T03:19:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/barclays-hires-ex-morgan-stanley-investment-banker-ueki-in-japan.html
Barclays Plc hired  Tsutomu Ueki , a
former Morgan Stanley merger-and-acquisition banker, to expand
investment banking in Japan, according to an internal memo
obtained by Bloomberg News.  Ueki, 44, joined Barclays Capital Japan Ltd.’s investment
banking division today as a managing director overseeing
insurance and specialty finance industries, the memo said. The
London-based bank confirmed the appointment in a statement.  During his tenure at Morgan Stanley, Ueki was involved in
transactions including the merger of Mitsui Sumitomo Insurance
Group, Aioi Insurance and Nissay Dowa General Insurance,
according to the statement. Previously Ueki had worked at
JPMorgan Chase & Co. and managed transactions such as Sony
Financial Holdings Inc.’s initial public offering, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
